virginia attorney general robert q harris contended 
he urged the justices to overturn a 4th us circuit court of 
appeals decision requiring the state to provide lawyers at taxpayer 
expense in socalled habeas corpus proceedings in state courts 
like other states virginia provides prison law libraries and 
assigns parttime lawyers to help all inmates prepare their 
secondround or collateral appeals in some cases volunteer 
lawyers are available 
